    "body": "### Problem\n\nOnly the filename is displayed:\n\n<img width=\"865\" height=\"561\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/327161ab-4a91-421c-8cdb-9195dc05adaa\" />\n\nCompare to ui1:\n\n<img width=\"865\" height=\"561\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a1fd21ba-0cf0-48f8-841d-2cff7baab847\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- `mkdir ./read_only`\n- `chmod -w ./read_only`\n- `nvim --clean ./read_only/test.txt`\n- `:lua require('vim._core.ui2').enable()`\n- `:w`\n\n`g<` will display the entire message, but there is no indication that there is more to see.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe error is not hidden.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev+246-d393975b0",
